1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,200
Let me ask you a question

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:03,733
You spent 200 yuan on an AI membership

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:04,733
Used it for a month

4
00:00:04,766 --> 00:00:06,233
And realized you barely use it at all

5
00:00:06,433 --> 00:00:07,400
It's about to expire

6
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:08,600
Will you renew

7
00:00:08,766 --> 00:00:09,900
If you say no

8
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:10,833
Then let me ask you this

9
00:00:10,966 --> 00:00:13,100
Why have you been renewing it for six months straight

10
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,666
You're not alone in this

11
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:19,666
Over 300 million people worldwide are paying for subscriptions they barely use

12
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:20,633
Netflix

13
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,566
ChatGPT

14
00:00:21,566 --> 00:00:22,300
Spotify

15
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:23,566
All kinds of cloud storage

16
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:27,200
Your bank card is bleeding money every month

17
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,800
And you don't even notice

18
00:00:28,966 --> 00:00:30,066
Let me do the math for you

19
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:32,400
How many subscriptions do you have on your phone right now

20
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,600
Five

21
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,466
Eight

22
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,700
Average 30 yuan per month each

23
00:00:36,966 --> 00:00:38,466
Five means 150 a month

24
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:41,200
That's 1800 yuan a year

25
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:43,233
But the ones you actually open every week

26
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,533
Are probably just one or two

27
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:45,800
The other three

28
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,366
You're just giving money away every month

29
00:00:47,566 --> 00:00:48,966
1800 yuan isn't much

30
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,466
But you're buying something every year

31
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,066
The illusion that you'll definitely use it someday

32
00:00:55,166 --> 00:00:56,466
Today I'm going to tell you

33
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,533
There's an economic principle manipulating your brain behind all this

34
00:00:59,866 --> 00:01:00,600
Understand it

35
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,000
And you can save at least a few thousand yuan every year

36
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,433
And this principle

37
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:06,166
Doesn't just save you money

38
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:09,666
It can help you make the hardest decisions in your life

39
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:11,066
In 1985

40
00:01:11,166 --> 00:01:13,866
Ohio University conducted an experiment

41
00:01:13,966 --> 00:01:16,300
When selling tickets at a theater

42
00:01:16,566 --> 00:01:18,733
They randomly gave discounts to some buyers

43
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,600
Some paid full price

44
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,000
15 yuan

45
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,700
Some got a discount

46
00:01:24,066 --> 00:01:24,866
8 yuan

47
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:27,100
And some only paid 2 yuan

48
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,566
Then they tracked attendance for an entire season

49
00:01:29,933 --> 00:01:32,066
To see who attended the most shows

50
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,666
Guess what they found

51
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:36,033
The people who paid 15 yuan full price

52
00:01:36,033 --> 00:01:37,466
Attended the most shows

53
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:39,300
The ones who paid 2 yuan

54
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:40,800
Actually went the least

55
00:01:40,966 --> 00:01:41,900
Logically

56
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,166
The ticket is already bought

57
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:44,500
No matter how much you paid

58
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,300
Going or not should only depend on whether you want to see it

59
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,200
Right

60
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,066
But it doesn't

61
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,900
The more you spend

62
00:01:50,966 --> 00:01:53,000
The more you feel like not going is a waste

63
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:55,133
Why do people think this way

64
00:01:55,166 --> 00:01:59,133
Nobel Prize winner Daniel Kahneman studied this his entire life

65
00:01:59,433 --> 00:02:00,233
He found that

66
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:02,266
The pain of losing something

67
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,166
Is twice as intense as the pleasure of gaining something

68
00:02:04,366 --> 00:02:06,366
The happiness of finding 100 yuan

69
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,066
Is nowhere near the pain of losing 100 yuan

70
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,400
So you don't really want to see the show

71
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,566
You just can't stand the pain of having wasted money

72
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:15,100
This is sunk cost

73
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:17,000
The economic definition is simple

74
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,500
Costs that have already occurred

75
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,100
And cannot be recovered

76
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,500
Are called sunk costs

77
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:23,900
Let me give you an example you might relate to more

78
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,400
You go to a buffet

79
00:02:25,933 --> 00:02:26,933
298 yuan per person

80
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,333
After you walk in

81
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:29,733
What's the first thing you think

82
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:31,066
I have to eat my money's worth

83
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:33,266
So you grab all the expensive stuff

84
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:34,666
Seafood

85
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:35,733
Steak

86
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,800
Sashimi

87
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,500
You're stuffed

88
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:39,566
But you won't stop

89
00:02:39,766 --> 00:02:40,566
Why

90
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:43,200
I haven't eaten 298 yuan worth yet

91
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,300
The result

92
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,133
You get acute gastroenteritis

93
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,300
Hospital bill is 800 yuan

94
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:50,733
The 298 buffet wasn't earned back

95
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:52,133
And you lost another 800 on top

96
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:53,766
When you paid that 298 yuan

97
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,200
The money was already gone

98
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,400
Whether you can eat your money's worth

99
00:02:56,533 --> 00:02:58,466
Has nothing to do with that 298 anymore

100
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,800
What you should really do

101
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:01,466
Is stop when you're comfortable

102
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,500
But sunk cost won't let you stop

103
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,600
Let me give you a more everyday example

104
00:03:05,766 --> 00:03:07,900
You spent 80 yuan on a movie ticket

105
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,233
Watched for 20 minutes

106
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,666
And realized the movie is terrible

107
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:11,666
What would you do

108
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,500
Most people would choose

109
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,100
To sit through it

110
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:16,400
What's the reason

111
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:17,400
I already paid for it

112
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,733
Not finishing it would be a waste

113
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:19,900
But think about it carefully

114
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:21,200
That 80 yuan

115
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,466
Whether you finish watching or not

116
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,566
Is already spent

117
00:03:23,566 --> 00:03:24,566
It's not coming back

118
00:03:24,766 --> 00:03:26,900
The real question to ask is

119
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,033
How do you want to spend

120
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,400
The next 90 minutes more valuably

121
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:32,800
Keep watching a bad movie

122
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,133
Or go for a walk

123
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:34,733
Read a book

124
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:35,800
Scroll on your phone for a bit

125
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,333
Any of these is better than sitting there suffering

126
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,366
The so-called sunk cost fallacy

127
00:03:40,366 --> 00:03:42,866
Is letting money that's already spent

128
00:03:42,966 --> 00:03:44,966
Hijack your future choices

129
00:03:44,966 --> 00:03:45,600
Now

130
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,966
Back to the AI topic

131
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:49,666
There are so many AI subscription services it's dizzying

132
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,633
ChatGPT

133
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:51,366
Claude

134
00:03:51,366 --> 00:03:52,233
Midjourney

135
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:52,733
Cursor

136
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:53,333
Copilot

137
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,166
Notion AI

138
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,400
Many people impulsively sign up for several

139
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,366
Try this one

140
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,533
Get that one too

141
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,066
Auto-charged every month

142
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,466
Until you forget about it

143
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:04,066
But when you check your screen time

144
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:07,066
You only used this tool for 15 minutes last week

145
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:08,466
You know you should cancel

146
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,966
But you just can't bring yourself to do it

147
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,800
Because there's a voice in your head saying

148
00:04:12,033 --> 00:04:13,900
I've already paid for six months

149
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,566
Canceling now would be a waste

150
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:16,500
Listen carefully

151
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,700
The money that's already sunk

152
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,333
Is not within your control

153
00:04:20,533 --> 00:04:23,233
But whether you keep throwing money into the water

154
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,500
Is entirely up to you

155
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,133
These two things must be separated

156
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:28,366
And the product managers at AI companies

157
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:31,000
Understand your psychology perfectly

158
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:34,500
They've designed three mechanisms specifically to lock you in

159
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:35,500
The first layer

160
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:36,900
Is called the annual discount

161
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,266
Save 40 percent with annual billing

162
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:39,533
You see that and think

163
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:40,100
Oh wow

164
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:41,166
Saving hundreds at once

165
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:41,900
What a deal

166
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,466
But what is it really

167
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:46,800
It's making your sunk cost enormous all at once

168
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:48,766
Once you pay the annual fee

169
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:49,966
And want to cancel midway

170
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,566
Haven't I wasted the money from previous months

171
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:53,466
See

172
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,533
The trap strikes again

173
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,766
Let me calculate for you

174
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,866
ChatGPT Plus is 20 dollars per month

175
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,733
Annual billing claims to save 40 percent

176
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:03,066
Looks like you save a lot

177
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:06,066
But what if you only actually use it for 3 months out of the year

178
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:08,300
You paid for 12 months

179
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,766
But only got 3 months of value

180
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,033
Saved money

181
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:12,600
You lost big time

182
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:13,766
The second layer

183
00:05:13,766 --> 00:05:15,300
Is called data lock-in

184
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,866
Your chat history

185
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:19,933
The custom prompts you spent a month perfecting

186
00:05:19,966 --> 00:05:21,166
Your usage habits

187
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,866
Are all stored inside

188
00:05:23,033 --> 00:05:24,266
Switch to another tool

189
00:05:24,766 --> 00:05:26,466
And you start from zero

190
00:05:26,566 --> 00:05:28,766
This isn't a money sunk cost anymore

191
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:31,366
This is a time and energy sunk cost

192
00:05:31,366 --> 00:05:32,100
Which hurts even more

193
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,300
The third layer

194
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,900
Is called tiered pricing

195
00:05:35,033 --> 00:05:36,500
First let you use it for free

196
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,900
Once you're used to it

197
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:40,566
Tell you that upgrading unlocks full features

198
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:42,966
You've already spent two weeks learning how to use it

199
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,733
Not upgrading now

200
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,600
Feels like the time spent was wasted

201
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:49,666
Let me tell you a real story

202
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,800
I didn't make this up

203
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:52,500
Go ask in the comments

204
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:53,700
Tons of people fell for it

205
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,200
A freelancer

206
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,600
Subscribed to ChatGPT

207
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,866
Midjourney

208
00:05:58,900 --> 00:05:59,700
Cursor

209
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,033
Notion AI

210
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:01,666
Copilot

211
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,600
Five AI tools

212
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:05,933
Monthly membership fees alone over 700 yuan

213
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,600
He thought he was an AI super user

214
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:09,600
Very cutting edge

215
00:06:09,766 --> 00:06:12,166
Then one day he checked his screen time

216
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:14,933
Last week he only actually opened ChatGPT

217
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,533
For less than 20 minutes

218
00:06:16,733 --> 00:06:17,766
The other four

219
00:06:17,766 --> 00:06:18,466
Zero

220
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,366
700 yuan

221
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,066
For 20 minutes of use

222
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:23,866
Open your subscription list right now and check

223
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,366
How many do you have

224
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:28,500
How many do you actually use

225
00:06:28,766 --> 00:06:30,266
Stack all three layers together

226
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,866
Money lock-in

227
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,300
Data lock-in

228
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:34,700
Habit lock-in

229
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,566
You're locked in a cycle of endless renewals

230
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,800
And you even think it's your own choice

231
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:40,933
You might think

232
00:06:41,566 --> 00:06:42,966
It's just a few memberships

233
00:06:42,966 --> 00:06:44,066
Cancel them and move on

234
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,300
Not a big deal

235
00:06:45,533 --> 00:06:48,266
But the truly terrifying thing about sunk cost isn't here

236
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,433
It's in the big decisions of your life

237
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:52,133
Where its impact is devastating

238
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,500
Let me give you three examples

239
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,000
See how many you've fallen for

240
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:55,933
First one

241
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:56,966
Getting stuck holding losing stocks

242
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,033
You bought a stock at 10 yuan

243
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:00,066
It dropped to 6

244
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,100
All your analysis tells you

245
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:03,533
This stock has no hope

246
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:04,600
But you just won't sell

247
00:07:04,766 --> 00:07:05,600
Why

248
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,800
I've already lost 40 percent

249
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,433
Selling now would be too painful

250
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:10,466
Let me wait a bit longer

251
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,666
Then it drops from 6 to 3

252
00:07:12,766 --> 00:07:14,133
From 3 to 1

253
00:07:14,333 --> 00:07:15,533
The numbers speak

254
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,733
The Shanghai Stock Exchange has statistics

255
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:21,766
Less than 10 percent of retail investors in A-shares are profitable long-term

256
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:24,066
Why do so many people lose money

257
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:26,066
One core reason is

258
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,766
They can't cut their losses

259
00:07:27,966 --> 00:07:29,133
Holding losing positions

260
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:30,266
Getting deeper and deeper

261
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,600
The deeper they go the less they sell

262
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,700
A vicious cycle

263
00:07:32,933 --> 00:07:35,300
The money lost when it was at 10 yuan

264
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,533
And the money you lost afterward

265
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,166
Are they related

266
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:39,900
No

267
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,766
They are two completely independent decisions

268
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,766
But sunk cost makes you tie them together

269
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:46,766
Second one

270
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,366
A relationship that isn't working

271
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,933
You've been together for three years

272
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:51,200
You know in your heart

273
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,300
This relationship has no future

274
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,733
But you can't let go

275
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,566
I've already invested three years of my youth

276
00:07:56,566 --> 00:07:57,500
If I leave now

277
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,200
Wasn't it all for nothing

278
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,833
The three years have already passed

279
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,033
Whether you stay or go

280
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,100
They're not coming back

281
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:04,433
The real question is

282
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:07,000
Are you willing to gamble another three years

283
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:08,066
Third one

284
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,900
A dead-end job

285
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:11,833
You've been at a company for five years

286
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:12,900
No growth

287
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:13,966
No raise

288
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:15,133
No hope in sight

289
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,100
But you won't leave

290
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:17,266
I've already been here five years

291
00:08:17,266 --> 00:08:18,600
Leaving now would be such a waste

292
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,566
Let me stick it out

293
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:20,700
Maybe things will get better

294
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:21,733
Fourth one

295
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,300
A training course that isn't right for you

296
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,066
You spent 20000 yuan on a coding bootcamp

297
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:27,766
After a few classes

298
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,700
You realize you can't keep up at all

299
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,933
What the teacher covers doesn't match your direction

300
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,500
But you won't drop the course

301
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,500
Why

302
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,633
I already paid 20000

303
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:38,200
Not finishing would be a waste

304
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:40,566
So you force yourself through three months

305
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:41,700
Three months of time

306
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,100
If you had done something else instead

307
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:45,500
Learn a skill that suits you better

308
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:47,666
Take on a project that builds experience

309
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,500
Or even just rest properly

310
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,566
Any of these is better than sitting through a class you don't understand

311
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:53,800
These four scenarios

312
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,200
Stocks

313
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,133
Relationships

314
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,100
Career

315
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,000
Education

316
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:00,966
Are all driven by the same thing underneath

317
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:04,700
You won't accept that past investments are unrecoverable

318
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,100
So you try to compensate with even more investment

319
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:08,400
But you're not compensating

320
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,900
You're doubling down on losses

321
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,100
Having said all this

322
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:12,266
How do you break free

323
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:13,700
I'll give you three questions

324
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:17,133
Every time you're at the crossroads of should I keep going

325
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,266
Pull them out and ask yourself

326
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:19,466
First question

327
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,166
The zero-based test

328
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:24,166
Imagine you're encountering this for the first time today

329
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:25,433
This stock

330
00:09:25,433 --> 00:09:26,100
This person

331
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,133
This job

332
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,466
This AI membership

333
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,866
Given the current situation

334
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,333
Would you still choose it

335
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,000
Forget how much you've already spent

336
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,533
How much time

337
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:34,400
How much emotion

338
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:35,900
Pretend you're starting from zero

339
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,100
What would you choose now

340
00:09:37,233 --> 00:09:38,733
If the answer is no

341
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,766
Then you know what to do

342
00:09:40,966 --> 00:09:41,800
Second question

343
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,000
The data check

344
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,400
Don't trust your feelings

345
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,266
Look at the data

346
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:46,366
AI membership

347
00:09:46,933 --> 00:09:49,566
How many times did you open it in the past 30 days

348
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:50,833
Not how many times you plan to use it

349
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:52,133
But how many times you actually used it

350
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:53,733
Open your screen time

351
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:54,766
Numbers don't lie

352
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,600
Stocks

353
00:09:55,766 --> 00:09:57,366
What's your stop-loss line

354
00:09:57,566 --> 00:09:58,366
Has it been hit

355
00:09:58,533 --> 00:09:59,333
Job

356
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,800
Did you learn anything new in the past year

357
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,766
Did you get a raise

358
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:05,566
Replace feeling okay with letting data decide

359
00:10:05,766 --> 00:10:07,366
And sunk cost can't fool you anymore

360
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:08,366
Third question

361
00:10:08,533 --> 00:10:09,733
Opportunity cost

362
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,400
There's another term in economics

363
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:12,800
Called opportunity cost

364
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:14,200
When you choose A

365
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,300
You lose the opportunity to do B

366
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:17,600
The same money

367
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,466
This time

368
00:10:18,466 --> 00:10:19,400
This energy

369
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:20,766
If not spent here

370
00:10:20,766 --> 00:10:21,900
What else could you do with it

371
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,266
Maybe that 200 yuan AI membership fee

372
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:26,866
Spent on another tool could double your ROI

373
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,700
Maybe the energy drained by this relationship

374
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:31,200
Would be better spent improving yourself

375
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:34,166
Maybe that extra year you stuck around at this company

376
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,466
Made you miss a better opportunity window

377
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:40,066
Sunk cost keeps you focused on what you've already spent

378
00:10:40,533 --> 00:10:43,500
Opportunity cost reminds you what you could still gain

379
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:44,933
Use them together

380
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:47,333
And it becomes very hard to make irrational decisions

381
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:49,200
Let me walk you through a scenario

382
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,000
You have an AI membership

383
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,733
200 yuan per month

384
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:54,400
You've renewed for 8 months already

385
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:55,966
Now you need to decide

386
00:10:56,566 --> 00:10:57,933
Whether to keep it

387
00:10:58,133 --> 00:10:59,466
Apply the zero-based test

388
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:01,800
Imagine seeing this tool for the first time today

389
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:03,500
Would you spend 200 yuan on it

390
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,933
You think about it probably not

391
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,366
Apply the data check

392
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,866
How many times did you open it in the past 30 days

393
00:11:09,966 --> 00:11:10,766
Twice

394
00:11:10,766 --> 00:11:12,566
Less than 10 minutes each time

395
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:13,900
Apply opportunity cost

396
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,700
If you save this 200 yuan

397
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:17,566
That's 2400 a year

398
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:20,266
Enough to buy a tool you actually use every day

399
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:21,600
After running through all three methods

400
00:11:21,633 --> 00:11:22,766
The answer is crystal clear

401
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:23,966
Cancel

402
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:24,900
By the way

403
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,200
After watching this video today

404
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,300
I suggest you do one thing immediately

405
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:30,300
Open your phone's subscription list

406
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,800
Run every membership through the zero-based test

407
00:11:33,366 --> 00:11:35,900
Imagine you're seeing each tool for the first time today

408
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,500
Would you still spend money on it

409
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:40,100
Anything you hesitate on for more than 3 seconds

410
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,066
Cancel immediately

411
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:43,300
Don't think about what if I need it next month

412
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:44,800
When you actually need it next month

413
00:11:44,966 --> 00:11:46,066
Just buy it then

414
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:48,400
Every yuan you save today

415
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,866
Is a raise you give yourself

416
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:54,300
The core essence of sunk cost comes down to one sentence

417
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:55,566
Things in the past

418
00:11:55,566 --> 00:11:57,066
Are not within your power to change

419
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,733
But things in the future

420
00:11:58,766 --> 00:12:00,400
Are entirely within your power to choose

421
00:12:00,566 --> 00:12:02,300
When you truly understand this

422
00:12:02,366 --> 00:12:05,666
You'll find that many decisions you've agonized over

423
00:12:05,966 --> 00:12:08,000
The answer has been clear all along

424
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,933
You just needed a reason

425
00:12:09,966 --> 00:12:11,133
To let go

426
00:12:11,533 --> 00:12:12,933
This video today

427
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:14,333
Is that reason

428
00:12:14,466 --> 00:12:15,266
Finally

429
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,333
Let me leave you with one thought

430
00:12:16,566 --> 00:12:17,966
Truly smart people

431
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,400
Aren't those who never make mistakes

432
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,166
But those who after making mistakes

433
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,700
Don't try to fix them with even bigger mistakes

434
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,166
Money already spent

435
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,300
Let it go

436
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,766
Time already wasted

437
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:28,800
Let it go

438
00:12:28,966 --> 00:12:29,933
What matters is

439
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:32,666
Where every next yuan

440
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:33,700
Every next minute

441
00:12:33,766 --> 00:12:34,600
Gets spent

442
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,966
If this video helped you

443
00:12:36,966 --> 00:12:37,833
Drop a follow

444
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,800
I tell one economics story every week

445
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,633
Helping you see through the mental traps

446
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:44,966
You step into every day but never notice

447
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:46,100
Next episode

448
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:49,766
We'll talk about why AI companies are giving things away for free

449
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,366
What's their real calculation

